:"G4632","lemma":"σκεῦος","translit":"skeûos","derivation":"of uncertain affinity;","strongs_def":"a vessel, implement, equipment or apparatus (literally or figuratively [specially, a wife as contributing to the usefulness of the husband])","kjv_def":"goods, sail, stuff, vessel","pos":"neuter noun","usage":"vessel(19x), goods(2x), stuff(1x), sail(1x)"},"G4625":{"id":"G4625","lemma":"σκάνδαλον","translit":"skándalon","derivation":"(\"scandal\"); probably from a derivative of G2578 (κάμπτω);","strongs_def":"a trap-stick (bent sapling), i.e. snare (figuratively, cause of displeasure or sin)","kjv_def":"occasion to fall (of stumbling), offence, thing that offends, stumblingblock","pos":"neuter noun","usage":"offence(9x)"},"G4642":{"id":"G4642","lemma":"σκληρός","translit":"sklērós","derivation":"from the base of G4628 (σκέλος);","strongs_def":"dry, i.e. hard or tough (figuratively, harsh, severe)","kjv_def":"fierce, hard","pos":"adjective","usage":"hard(5x), fierce(1x)"},"G4686":{"id":"G4686","lemma":"σπεῖρα","translit":"speîra","derivation":"of immediate Latin origin, but ultimately a derivative of G138 (αἱρέομαι) in the sense of its cognate G1507 (εἱλίσσω);","strongs_def":"a coil (spira, \"spire\"), i.e. (figuratively) a mass of men (a Roman military cohort; also (by analogy) a squad of Levitical janitors)","kjv_def":"band","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"band(7x)"},"G4679":{"id":"G4679","lemma":"σοφίζω","translit":"sophízō","derivation":"from G4680 (σοφός);","strongs_def":"to render wise; in a sinister acceptation, to form \"sophisms\", i.e. continue plausible error","kjv_def":"cunningly devised, make wise"},"G4662":{"id":"G4662","lemma":"σκωληκόβρωτος","translit":"skōlēkóbrōtos","derivation":"from G4663 (σκώληξ) and a derivative of G977 (βιβρώσκω);","strongs_def":"worm-eaten, i.e. diseased with maggots","kjv_def":"eaten of worms","pos":"adjective"},"G4696":{"id":"G4696","lemma":"σπίλος","translit":"spílos","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"a stain or blemish, i.e. (figuratively) defect, disgrace","kjv_def":"spot","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"defile(1x), spot(1x)"},"G4695":{"id":"G4695","lemma":"σπιλόω","translit":"spilóō","derivation":"from G4696 (σπίλος);","strongs_def":"to stain or soil (literally or figuratively)","kjv_def":"defile, spot","pos":"verb","usage":"spot(2x)"},"G4656":{"id":"G4656","lemma":"σκοτόω","translit":"skotóō","derivation":"from G4655 (σκότος);","strongs_def":"to obscure or blind (literally or figuratively)","kjv_def":"be full of darkness","pos":"verb"},"G4658":{"id":"G4658","lemma":"Σκύθης","translit":"Skýthēs","derivation":"probably of foreign origin;","strongs_def":"a Scythene or Scythian, i.e. (by implication) a savage","kjv_def":"Scythian","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Scythian(1x)"},"G4651":{"id":"G4651","lemma":"σκορπίος","translit":"skorpíos","derivation":"probably from an obsolete (perhaps strengthened from the base of G4649 (σκοπός) and meaning to pierce);","strongs_def":"a \"scorpion\" (from its sting)","kjv_def":"scorpion","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"scorpion(5x)"},"G4624":{"id":"G4624","lemma":"σκανδαλίζω","translit":"skandalízō","derivation":"from G4625 (σκάνδαλον);","strongs_def":"to entrap, i.e. trip up (figuratively, stumble (transitively) or entice to sin, apostasy or displeasure)","kjv_def":"(make to) offend","pos":"verb","usage":"offend(28x)"},"G4622":{"id":"G4622","lemma":"Σιών","translit":"Siṓn","derivation":"of Hebrew origin (H06726);","strongs_def":"Sion (i.e. Tsijon), a hill of Jerusalem; figuratively, the Church (militant or triumphant)","kjv_def":"Sion","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Sion(7x)"},"G4601":{"id":"G4601","lemma":"σιγάω","translit":"sigáō","derivation":"from G4602 (σιγή);","strongs_def":"to keep silent (transitively or intransitively)","kjv_def":"keep close (secret, silence), hold peace","pos":"verb"},"G4637":{"id":"G4637","lemma":"σκηνόω","translit":"skēnóō","derivation":"from G4636 (σκῆνος);","strongs_def":"to tent or encamp, i.e. (figuratively) to occupy (as a mansion) or (specially), to reside (as God did in the Tabernacle of old, a symbol of protection and communion)","kjv_def":"dwell","pos":"verb","usage":"dwell(5x)"},"G4672":{"id":"G4672","lemma":"Σολομών","translit":"Solomṓn","derivation":"of Hebrew origin (H08010);","strongs_def":"Solomon (i.e. Shelomoh), the son of David","kjv_def":"Solomon","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Solomon(12x)"},"G4659":{"id":"G4659","lemma":"σκυθρωπός","translit":"skythrōpós","derivation":"from (sullen) and a derivative of G3700 (ὀπτάνομαι);","strongs_def":"angry-visaged, i.e. gloomy or affecting a mournful appearance","kjv_def":"of a sad countenance","pos":"adjective","usage":"sad(1x)"},"G4690":{"id":"G4690","lemma":"σπέρμα","translit":"spérma","derivation":"from G4687 (σπείρω);","strongs_def":"something sown, i.e. seed (including the male \"sperm\"); by implication, offspring; specially, a remnant (figuratively, as if kept over for planting)","kjv_def":"issue, seed","pos":"neuter noun","usage":"seed(43x), issue(1x)"},"G4604":{"id":"G4604","lemma":"σίδηρος","translit":"sídēros","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"iron","kjv_def":"iron","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"iron(1x)"},"G4646":{"id":"G4646","lemma":"σκολιός","translit":"skoliós","derivation":"from the base of G4628 (σκέλος);","strongs_def":"warped, i.e. winding; figuratively, perverse","kjv_def":"crooked, froward, untoward","pos":"adjective","usage":"crooked(2x), untoward(1x), froward(1x)"},"G4692":{"id":"G4692","lemma":"σπεύδω","translit":"speúdō","derivation":"probably strengthened from G4228 (πούς);","strongs_def":"to \"speed\" (\"study\"), i.e. urge on (diligently or earnestly); by implication, to await eagerly","kjv_def":"(make, with) haste unto","pos":"verb","usage":"haste(1x)"},"G4682":{"id":"G4682","lemma":"σπαράσσω","translit":"sparássō","derivation":"prolongation from (to grasp;","strongs_def":"apparently strengthened from G4685 (σπάω) through the idea of spasmodic contraction); to mangle, i.e. convluse with epilepsy","kjv_def":"rend, tear","pos":"verb","usage":"tear(3x), rend(1x)"},"G4627":{"id":"G4627","lemma":"σκάφη","translit":"skáphē","strongs_def":"a \"skiff\" (as if dug out), or yawl (carried aboard a large vessel for landing)","kjv_def":"boat","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"boat(3x)"},"G4615":{"id":"G4615","lemma":"σίναπι","translit":"sínapi","derivation":"perhaps from (to hurt, i.e. sting);","strongs_def":"mustard (the plant)","kjv_def":"mustard","pos":"neuter noun"},"G4698":{"id":"G4698","lemma":"σπλάγχνον","translit":"splánchnon","derivation":"probably strengthened from (the \"spleen\");","strongs_def":"an intestine (plural); figuratively, pity or sympathy","kjv_def":"bowels, inward affection, + tender mercy","pos":"neuter noun","usage":"bowels(9x)"},"G4620":{"id":"G4620","lemma":"σιτόμετρον","translit":"sitómetron","derivation":"from G4621 (σῖτος) and G3358 (μέτρον);","strongs_def":"a grain-measure, i.e. (by implication) ration (allowance of food)","kjv_def":"portion of meat","pos":"neuter noun"},"G4676":{"id":"G4676","lemma":"σουδάριον","translit":"soudárion","derivation":"of Latin origin;","strongs_def":"a sudarium (sweat-cloth), i.e. towel (for wiping the perspiration from the face, or binding the face of a corpse)","kjv_def":"handkerchief, napkin","pos":"neuter noun","usage":"napkin(3x), handkerchief(1x)"},"G4607":{"id":"G4607","lemma":"σικάριος","translit":"sikários","derivation":"of Latin origin;","strongs_def":"a dagger-man or assassin; a freebooter (Jewish fanatic outlawed by the Romans)","kjv_def":"murderer"},"G4643":{"id":"G4643","lemma":"σκληρότης","translit":"sklērótēs","derivation":"from G4642 (σκληρός);","strongs_def":"callousness, i.e. (figuratively) stubbornness","kjv_def":"hardness","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"hardness(1x)"},"G4675":{"id":"G4675","lemma":"σοῦ","translit":"soû","derivation":"genitive case of G4771 (σύ);","strongs_def":"of thee, thy","kjv_def":"X home, thee, thine (own), thou, thy","pos":"pronoun","usage":"thy(358x), thee(76x), thine(50x), thou(6x)"},"G4694":{"id":"G4694","lemma":"σπιλάς","translit":"spilás","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"a ledge or reef of rock in the sea","kjv_def":"spot (by confusion with G4696 (σπίλος))","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"spot(1x)"},"G4614":{"id":"G4614","lemma":"Σινᾶ","translit":"Sinâ","derivation":"of Hebrew origin (H05514);","strongs_def":"Sina (i.e. Sinai), a mountain in Arabia","kjv_def":"Sina","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Sina(2x), Sinai(2x)"},"G4673":{"id":"G4673","lemma":"σορός","translit":"sorós","derivation":"probably akin to the base of G4987 (σωρεύω);","strongs_def":"a funereal receptacle (urn, coffin), i.e. (by analogy) a bier","kjv_def":"bier","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"bier(1x)"},"G4691":{"id":"G4691","lemma":"σπερμολόγος","translit":"spermológos","derivation":"from G4690 (σπέρμα) and G3004 (λέγω);","strongs_def":"a seed-picker (as the crow), i.e. (figuratively) a sponger, loafer (specially, a gossip or trifler in talk)","kjv_def":"babbler","pos":"adjective","usage":"babbler(1x)"},"G4668":{"id":"G4668","lemma":"Σμυρναῖος","translit":"Smyrnaîos","derivation":"from G4667 (Σμύρνα);","strongs_def":"a Smyrnæan","kjv_def":"in Smyrna","pos":"adjective","usage":"Smyrna(1x)"},"G4630":{"id":"G4630","lemma":"Σκευᾶς","translit":"Skeuâs","derivation":"apparently of Latin origin;","strongs_def":"left-handed; Scevas (i.e. Scævus), an Israelite","kjv_def":"Sceva","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Sceva(1x)"},"G4660":{"id":"G4660","lemma":"σκύλλω","translit":"skýllō","derivation":"apparently a primary verb;","strongs_def":"to flay, i.e. (figuratively) to harass","kjv_def":"trouble(self)","pos":"verb","usage":"trouble(2x)"},"G4653":{"id":"G4653","lemma":"σκοτία","translit":"skotía","derivation":"from G4655 (σκότος);","strongs_def":"dimness, obscurity (literally or figuratively)","kjv_def":"dark(-ness)","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"darkness(14x), dark(2x)"},