ine);","strongs_def":"lily; Susannah (i.e. Shoshannah), an Israelitess","kjv_def":"Susanna","pos":"proper feminine noun","usage":"Susanna(1x)"},"G4666":{"id":"G4666","lemma":"σμύρνα","translit":"smýrna","derivation":"apparently strengthened for G3464 (μύρον);","strongs_def":"myrrh","kjv_def":"myrrh","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"myrrh(2x)"},"G4626":{"id":"G4626","lemma":"σκάπτω","translit":"skáptō","derivation":"apparently a primary verb;","strongs_def":"to dig","kjv_def":"dig","pos":"verb","usage":"dig(3x)"},"G4610":{"id":"G4610","lemma":"Σιλουανός","translit":"Silouanós","derivation":"of Latin origin;","strongs_def":"\"silvan\"; Silvanus, a Christian","kjv_def":"Silvanus"},"G4613":{"id":"G4613","lemma":"Σίμων","translit":"Símōn","derivation":"of Hebrew origin (H08095);","strongs_def":"Simon (i.e. Shimon), the name of nine Israelites","kjv_def":"Simon","pos":"proper masculine noun"},"G4608":{"id":"G4608","lemma":"σίκερα","translit":"síkera","derivation":"of Hebrew origin (H07941);","strongs_def":"an intoxicant, i.e. intensely fermented liquor","kjv_def":"strong drink","pos":"neuter noun"},"G4623":{"id":"G4623","lemma":"σιωπάω","translit":"siōpáō","derivation":"from (silence, i.e. a hush;","strongs_def":"properly, muteness, i.e. involuntary stillness, or inability to speak; and thus differing from G4602 (σιγή), which is rather a voluntary refusal or indisposition to speak, although the terms are often used synonymously); to be dumb (but not deaf also, like 2974 properly); figuratively, to be calm (as quiet water)","kjv_def":"dumb, (hold) peace","pos":"verb","usage":"peace(1x), dumb(1x)"},"G4634":{"id":"G4634","lemma":"σκηνοπηγία","translit":"skēnopēgía","derivation":"from G4636 (σκῆνος) and G4078 (πήγνυμι);","strongs_def":"the Festival of Tabernacles (so called from the custom of erecting booths for temporary homes)","kjv_def":"tabernacles","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"tabernacles(1x)"},"G4661":{"id":"G4661","lemma":"σκῦλον","translit":"skŷlon","derivation":"neuter from G4660 (σκύλλω);","strongs_def":"something stripped (as a hide), i.e. booty","kjv_def":"spoil"},"G4687":{"id":"G4687","lemma":"σπείρω","translit":"speírō","derivation":"probably strengthened from G4685 (σπάω) (through the idea of extending);","strongs_def":"to scatter, i.e. sow (literally or figuratively)","kjv_def":"sow(- er), receive seed","pos":"verb","usage":"sow(43x), sower(6x)"},"G4602":{"id":"G4602","lemma":"σιγή","translit":"sigḗ","derivation":"apparently from (to hiss, i.e. hist or hush);","strongs_def":"silence","kjv_def":"silence","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"silence(2x)"}}